rules: Rule1: Provided that the electronic device meets standards, the drug is not recalled.
Rule2: Whenever the electronic device is calibrated, it meets standards.
Rule3: If the manufacturing process is approved, then the clinical trial does not fail.
Rule4: Provided that the quality control is approved, the clinical trial does not fail.
Rule5: The drug is on the market, or the manufacturing process is approved, or the quality control is approved.
Rule6: If the regulatory submission is approved, then the electronic device is calibrated.
Rule7: Either the regulatory submission is approved or the alternative submission is approved.
Rule8: Provided that the alternative submission is approved, the drug is not recalled.
Rule9: If it is not the case that the certified technician implies that a trained technician leads to either patented artwork or no clinical trial failure, then the project is terminated.
Rule10: Whenever it is false that the drug is profitable or the manufacturing process is approved or the quality control is approved, the drug is recalled.
Rule11: If it is not the case that the project not being funded implies an approved clinical trial, then the clinical trial fails.
Rule12: If the project is not funded, then the clinical trial is not approved.
